<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1266.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-10"><hi rend="italic">April 10,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Vice President Corral has been granted leave of absence for eight months
                            by Congress, and he will depart for Europe within a few days. As he did
                            not resign the situation is further complicated. [Revolutionist attacks
                            reported.] The governors of most of the Mexican States and their
                            subordinates are being replaced.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>